<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="1067" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1067">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/173</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Representative <persName type="to">Rodgers</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-07T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>125. Consul, Nogales, reports decree 56, dated May 18, signed by Calles,
                            given to press Saturday, provides all mining properties in State
                            continuing idle more than 30 days from date of decree subject seizure
                            and operation by State.</p>
                        <p>Refer your No. 84, May 23, 5 p.m., and request immediate issuance similar
                            orders this case.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>